    • Method Detail

      • deleteLocalizationIfEmpty

        public boolean deleteLocalizationIfEmpty()
                                  throws LocaleSourceException
        Convenience method to delete a localization if the text captured from the user is an empty string. This method will not delete a localization for a static key. This could delete the last localization, therefore care should be taken for when this is called in related to updateAndGetLocalizedObjectKey().
        Returns:
        true if the LOK was deleted or already NULL; false otherwise..
        Throws:
        LocaleSourceException - if the update or insert failed or no locale source is available.

      • getHTMLElement

        public Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

        Specified by:

        Overrides:

        the element.

      • getLocalizedObjectKey

        public LocalizedObjectKey getLocalizedObjectKey()
        Get the localized object key currently stored in the component. This will either be null, the object set with setLocalizedObjectKey(LocalizedObjectKey), or a possibly a new LocalizedObjectKey as a result of calling updateAndGetLocalizedObjectKey().
        Returns:
        a LocalizedObjectKey. To check for a null key, call LocalizedObjectKey.isNull(Object) on the returned object.

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called when a Component is first attached to a WindowManager. This means the Component should have valid return values from getApplication(), getLocaleContext(), getParent(). It is preferable to have all construction of the Component go here since a valid LocaleContext, Application object, etc., are available.

        When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class init(). init() is called only once for each Component. The parent component will have been init()ed before init() is called.

        NOTE: Do not call this method from application code. It is meant to be called by the WindowManager only.

        Specified by:
        init in interface Component
        Overrides:
        init in class Field

      • updateAndGetLocalizedObjectKey

        public LocalizedObjectKey updateAndGetLocalizedObjectKey()
                                                  throws LocaleSourceException
        Get the LocalizedObjectKey. This will update the data in the LocaleSource if necessary. If the key set in setLocalizedObjectKey(LocalizedObjectKey) was a static key or null then a new LocalizedObjectKey will be created when this method is called.

        If there is no text entered, then the properties: isInsertLocalizedObjectKeyWhenEmpty() and isUpdateLocalizedObjectKeyWhenEmpty() control whether any data is inserted or updated.

        Returns:
        the LocalizedObjectKey. May be null. If called before initialization, then no updates are made.
        Throws:
        LocaleSourceException - if the update or insert failed or no locale source is available.

        Description copied from interface: Component

        Normally called by the medium to make sure the component is in a valid state before updating the medium. Other classes may safely call as needed. Note however that validating may take a substantial amount of work depending on the subclass implementation!.

        NOTE: When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class validate() as the last statement in the overridden method.
